      <task xml:id="exer-cups-linear">
        <statement>
          <p>
            In the table above, which set of data is perfectly linear? How do you know?
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Find an equation to fit the linear data you chose in <xref ref="exer-cups-linear"/> (see <xref ref="exer-cups-desmos-class"/>). Explain both the slope and <m>y</m>-intercept in terms of stacked cups.
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task xml:id="exer-cups-height">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Use the equation you found to determine the internal height of a package that will contain 50 cups. Show and explain your work.
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task xml:id="exer-cups-num-cups">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Use the equation you found to determine the number of stacked cups that will fit inside a package with internal height of 100 <init>cm</init>. Show and explain your work.
          </p>
        </statement>
